    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Geometric patterns of shapes, covered on a plane, without gaps or overlaps. Used with computer design and mathematics, as opposed to the physical act of creating a mosaic of 3-D tiles. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000094828/Getty Vocabulary Program rules</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047416/Emmer, The Visual Mind (1993)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Motivos de figuras geométricas, que cubre un plano, quedando montados unos sobre otros o sin espacio. Usado para el diseño y matemática computacional, en oposición al acto físico de crear un mosaico de azulejos tridimensionales.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Geometrische patronen van vormen die een oppervlak bedekken, zonder overlapping of ruimten ertussen. Wordt gebruikt bij computerontwerpen en in de wiskunde. Het gaat hier dus niet om het fysiek creëren van een mozaïek van driedimensionale tegels.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>由覆蓋在平面上、沒有空隙或部分重疊的形狀所組合而成的幾何圖形。這是電腦設計和數學上的用詞，相對於實際創作出一片由立體的瓷磚所組合而成的馬賽克。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
